==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oviferous
<hw>O*vif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ov</ets>um
+ <ets>-ferous</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ovif⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Egg-bearing; -- applied particularly to certain
receptacles, as in Crustacea, that retain the eggs after they have been
excluded from the formative organs, until they are hatched.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oviform</ent>⟦br⟧
